{
    "chapter": 81,
    "verses": {
        "1": {
            "verses": {
                "81:1": {
                    "id": 1
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>When the sun is folded away, enfolded and stripped of its light,</p>"
        },
        "2": {
            "verses": {
                "81:2": {
                    "id": 2
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the stars scatter, [when] they are extinguished and hurtle down towards the earth,</p>"
        },
        "3": {
            "verses": {
                "81:3": {
                    "id": 3
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the mountains are set in motion, [when] they are blown away from the face of the earth, becoming as scattered dust,</p>"
        },
        "4": {
            "verses": {
                "81:4": {
                    "id": 4
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the pregnant camels are neglected, abandoned without a herdsman or anyone to milk them, on account of the matter that has come over them — even though [previously] no wealth was dearer to them than these [pregnant camels];</p>"
        },
        "5": {
            "verses": {
                "81:5": {
                    "id": 5
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the wild beasts are mustered, [when they are] brought together after being resurrected so that each of them may retaliate against the other, before becoming dust;</p>"
        },
        "6": {
            "verses": {
                "81:6": {
                    "id": 6
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the seas are set afire (read sujirat or sujjirat), [when] they are set alight and become [a mass of] fire;</p>"
        },
        "7": {
            "verses": {
                "81:7": {
                    "id": 7
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the souls are coupled, [when they are] paired up with their bodies;</p>"
        },
        "8": {
            "verses": {
                "81:8": {
                    "id": 8
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the girl buried-alive, the young girl buried alive for fear of shame and impoverishment, asks — in rebuke of its slayer —</p>"
        },
        "9": {
            "verses": {
                "81:9": {
                    "id": 9
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>for what sin she was slain (sa'alat, `asks': a variant reading has su'ilat, `[she] is asked', narrating the address directed to her, to which she then responds by saying, `I was slain without [having committed] any sin');</p>"
        },
        "10": {
            "verses": {
                "81:10": {
                    "id": 10
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the scrolls, the scrolls containing the deeds, are unrolled (read nushirat or nushshirat), [when they are] unfolded and spread out;</p>"
        },
        "11": {
            "verses": {
                "81:11": {
                    "id": 11
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the heaven is stripped off, torn away from its place, just as the skin of a sheep is stripped off;</p>"
        },
        "12": {
            "verses": {
                "81:12": {
                    "id": 12
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and when the Hell-fire is set ablaze (read su`irat or su``irat), [when it is] set alight;</p>"
        },
        "13": {
            "verses": {
                "81:13": {
                    "id": 13
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>and when Paradise is brought near, [when it is] brought close to those who have merited it, that they may enter it (the response to idh, `when', at the beginning of the sra and all that has been supplemented thereto is [the following]):</h2>"
        },
        "14": {
            "verses": {
                "81:14": {
                    "id": 14
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>[then] a soul, every soul, at the time of the [occurrence of the] things mentioned, which is the Day of Resurrection, will know what it has presented, of good or evil.</p>"
        },
        "15": {
            "verses": {
                "81:15": {
                    "id": 15
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<h2>So I swear (fa-l: l is extra) by the receding [planets],</h2>"
        },
        "16": {
            "verses": {
                "81:16": {
                    "id": 16
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>the movers, the setters, that is, the five planets: Saturn, Jupiter, Mars, Venus and Mercury (takhnusu means `they sink away' during their orbit, whereas we see stars at the end of their zodiacal course return to the start; taknisu means that they enter their kins, `hideaway', in other words, they retreat into their setting- places);</p>"
        },
        "17": {
            "verses": {
                "81:17": {
                    "id": 17
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and [by] the night as it approaches, as it falls with its darkness, or [it means] as it recedes;</p>"
        },
        "18": {
            "verses": {
                "81:18": {
                    "id": 18
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and [by] the dawn as it breathes, [as] it extends until it becomes broad daylight,</p>"
        },
        "19": {
            "verses": {
                "81:19": {
                    "id": 19
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>truly this, Qur'n, is the word of a messenger [who is] noble, in the sight of God, exalted be He — this being [the messenger] Gabriel (it [qawl, `word'] has been annexed to him, because he descends with it),</p>"
        },
        "20": {
            "verses": {
                "81:20": {
                    "id": 20
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>powerful, one of mighty powers, eminent, one of eminent status (maknin is semantically connected `inda, `in the presence of') in the presence of the Lord of the Throne, that is, God, exalted be He;</p>"
        },
        "21": {
            "verses": {
                "81:21": {
                    "id": 21
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>obeyed there, the angels obey him in the heavens, trustworthy, with the Revelation.</p>"
        },
        "22": {
            "verses": {
                "81:22": {
                    "id": 22
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And your companion, Muhammad (s) (wa-m shibukum: a supplement to [the clause from] innahu, `truly this is', up to the last of the oath clauses) is not a madman, as you claim.</p>"
        },
        "23": {
            "verses": {
                "81:23": {
                    "id": 23
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>For verily he, Muhammad (s), saw him, Gabriel, in the form in which he was created, on the clear horizon, the highest one, towards the east;</p>"
        },
        "24": {
            "verses": {
                "81:24": {
                    "id": 24
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>and he, Muhammad (s), is not to be accused of [knowing] the Unseen, what is hidden of the revelation and the tidings of the heaven (a variant reading [for bi-zannin] has bi-dannin, meaning that he is not `niggardly' [with the Unseen] so as to reduce something of it [and not disclose it]).</p>"
        },
        "25": {
            "verses": {
                "81:25": {
                    "id": 25
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>And it, that is, the Qur'n, is not the word of an accursed satan, eavesdropping stealthily.</p>"
        },
        "26": {
            "verses": {
                "81:26": {
                    "id": 26
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>So where are you going? So what path are you going to follow in repudiating the Qur'n and turning away from it?</p>"
        },
        "27": {
            "verses": {
                "81:27": {
                    "id": 27
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>It is only a reminder, an admonition, for all worlds, [those of] mankind and jinn,</p>"
        },
        "28": {
            "verses": {
                "81:28": {
                    "id": 28
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>for those of you who (li-man sh'a minkum is a substitution for li'l-`lamna, `for all worlds', using the same preposition) wish to go straight, by following the truth;</p>"
        },
        "29": {
            "verses": {
                "81:29": {
                    "id": 29
                }
            },
            "resource_id": 125,
            "resource_name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
            "language_id": 38,
            "slug": "en_jalalayn",
            "translated_name": {
                "name": "Tafsir En Jalalayn",
                "language_name": "english"
            },
            "text": "<p>but you will not [wish], to go straight along the [path of] truth, unless God, the Lord of the Worlds, [of all] creatures, wills, that you should go straight along it. Meccan, consisting of 19 verses.</p>"
        }
    }
}